From: kintera diagnostics
Date: 2026-05-24
Subject: Dump full PSTOR / DSTOR per species per altitude for transport diagnostic

KB writes per-species per-altitude PSTOR (production rate) and DSTOR
(destruction rate, signed negative) into in-memory arrays inside
OUTPUT_IMP — but only the top-3 contributing reactions per species
per altitude are persisted to prod+loss/<species>_{prod,loss}.dat.

This patch adds a second pass that writes the FULL summed PSTOR and
DSTOR per (species, altitude) cell to prod+loss/_full_pstor_dstor.dat.

Why we want it:
  At steady state, transport_div(species, k) = -(PSTOR + DSTOR)(species, k)
  for interior cells. With the top-3 prod+loss/ files this can't be
  computed reliably (the tail reactions are dropped). The dumped
  full PSTOR/DSTOR closes the diagnostic loop so kintera's transport
  matrix (build_transport_matrix.matvec) can be compared directly
  against KB's transport divergence at the converged state.

Effect:
  - New file: prod+loss/_full_pstor_dstor.dat
  - One line per (species, altitude) cell, in IV / alt_idx order.
  - Columns: IV, alt_idx, PSTOR (cm^-3 s^-1), DSTOR (cm^-3 s^-1).
  - The dump file is opened with STATUS='REPLACE' on each pass through
    OUTPUT_IMP so the LAST pass (final flow species) wins.
  - Does NOT affect the KB simulation state.

How to apply (from the KB checkout root):
  patch -p1 < diagnostics/kb_patches/02-full-pstor-dstor-dump.patch

Consumer:
  diagnostic_tools/transport_vs_kb.py reads
  prod+loss/_full_pstor_dstor.dat, reconstructs -(PSTOR + DSTOR) per
  species per altitude, and compares against kintera's transport
  divergence on the same KB-converged state.

Finding from running this diagnostic (2026-05-24):
  3641 interior (species, level) cells. Median |kt − kb|/max ratio = 1.0,
  90th pctile = 1.004, only 0.3% of cells with rel diff < 0.1. The
  pattern is opposite-sign at almost all cells, which is the signature
  of kintera doing ∂_z(K ∂_z c) while KB does ∂_z(K n_tot ∂_z(c/n_tot))
  (per kinetgen2X.F:15531 "diffusion uses xn = mixing ratio"). Logged
  in MEMORY.md under project_kintera_transport_form.md.

---
 src/KINETGENX/kinetgen1X.F | 34 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 34 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/KINETGENX/kinetgen1X.F b/src/KINETGENX/kinetgen1X.F
--- a/src/KINETGENX/kinetgen1X.F
+++ b/src/KINETGENX/kinetgen1X.F
@@ -10996,6 +10996,40 @@
              enddo
              close(89)
  8888     continue
+
+! Full per-species per-altitude PSTOR/DSTOR dump (sam 2026-05-24):
+! Each pass overwrites; final file (last pass) contains chem prod/loss
+! summed over ALL reactions. At steady state, transport_div(species,k)
+! = DSTOR(species,k) - PSTOR(species,k) for non-boundary species. Used
+! by diagnostic_tools/snapshot_transport_balance.py to verify kintera's
+! transport divergence against KB.
+          OPEN(94, FILE='prod+loss/_full_pstor_dstor.dat',
+     >         STATUS='REPLACE')
+          WRITE(94,*) 'IV   alt_idx   PSTOR(cm^-3 s^-1)' //
+     >                '   DSTOR(cm^-3 s^-1)'
+          DO J = 1,NVARY
+            IV = IVARY(J)
+            DO K = 1,NALT
+              WRITE(94,'(I5,2X,I4,2(2X,1PE13.5))') IV, K,
+     >          PSTOR(IV,1,1,K), DSTOR(IV,1,1,K)
+            ENDDO
+          ENDDO
+          CLOSE(94)
+
+! Full SRATE dump (sam 2026-05-24): per-reaction per-altitude rates.
+! Used to verify whether KB's prod+loss header "rxn 195" really uses
+! the formula we expect, or whether some other ZK slot is leaking in.
+          OPEN(95, FILE='prod+loss/_full_srate.dat',
+     >         STATUS='REPLACE')
+          WRITE(95,*) 'rxn  alt_idx  SRATE(cm^-3 s^-1)'
+          DO IX = 1,NREACT
+            DO K = 1,NALT
+              IF (SRATE(IX,1,1,K) .NE. 0.0) THEN
+                WRITE(95,'(I5,2X,I4,2X,1PE13.5)') IX, K,
+     >            SRATE(IX,1,1,K)
+              ENDIF
+            ENDDO
+          ENDDO
+          CLOSE(95)

           DO 2639 IX=1,NREACT
             DO 2637 IY=1,NVARY
